Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Decision No 88/390/EEC of 11 July 1988 on special support for the development of agricultural statistics in Ireland (1), as last amended by Decision 89/623/EEC (2), and in particular Article 4 thereof,
Whereas, as required by Article 4 (1) of the said Decision the Irish Government has submitted the annual programme of measures planned for 1991;
Whereas the programme that has been submitted is such as to attain the objectives of organizing in Ireland a system of surveys on agricultural matters which will satisfy Community requirements in respect of statistical information in this field;
Whereas the Irish Government has also submitted a report on the execution of the preceding annual programme;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Decision are in agreement with the opinion of the Standing Committee on Agricultural Statistics,
